14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1230 of Title 36, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. For purposes of this act:
19 1. "Assignment agreement" means any instrument by which post-
20 loss benefits under an auto, or residential or commercial property
21 insurance, including, but not limited to, any right of action
22 against the insurer or any proceeds acquired from the insurer, are
23 assigned, transferred, or acquired in any other manner, in whole or
24 in part, to or from a person providing services, including, but not
